headline: Week’s Best: AI Slams Wealth Management Stocks
summary: Investors have been on guard against disruptive artificial intelligence—and ready to dump shares when they perceive threats.  On Tuesday, it was the wealth management sector’s turn to get hammered.  Shares of  Charles Schwab  LPL Financial  and other wealth management companies took a licking after investors appeared to latch on to news that Altruist, a company that holds assets on behalf of financial advisors, had launched a new AI tax planning tool that some advisors view as groundbreaking.
